This paper deals with natural language processing and neural networks, which are typically covered in the Computer Science sub-category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning and word embeddings, which are relevant to the sub-categories of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on a specific task, temporal relation extraction, which falls under the sub-category of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses a linguistic resource, a part-of-speech tagger, which is relevant to the sub-category of "Information Retrieval" (cs.IR).
